qas.question: In what month is the university's scavenger hunt?
In what year did the scavenger hunt begin?
What is the name of the winter festival held in January that is based on fitness?
What is the name of the university's summer festival?
What has the university held since 1963 where large teams find items from a list?
What has been held since 1987, taking over the campus for 7-10 days with exhibitions?
What is held ever February at the university?
What is the university's winter carnival and concert called?
Which debate has been organized by the U of C since 1987?

context: Every May since 1987, the University of Chicago has held the University of Chicago Scavenger Hunt, in which large teams of students compete to obtain notoriously esoteric items from a list. Since 1963, the Festival of the Arts (FOTA) takes over campus for 7–10 days of exhibitions and interactive artistic endeavors. Every January, the university holds a week-long winter festival, Kuviasungnerk/Kangeiko, which include early morning exercise routines and fitness workshops. The university also annually holds a summer carnival and concert called Summer Breeze that hosts outside musicians, and is home to Doc Films, a student film society founded in 1932 that screens films nightly at the university. Since 1946, the university has organized the Latke-Hamantash Debate, which involves humorous discussions about the relative merits and meanings of latkes and hamantashen.
